rComments: Great prof, one of the best at UofT. Amazing lectures and very understanding & helpful. As others have mentioned, the marks are TA dependent but she is very likely to remark.

Very articulate and intelligent woman, and her course is meticulously designed to explore the idea of gender and crime to its fullest potential. The quizzes force you to engage with the readings, and the final paper is an entertaining one to write. Overall, this a great course and Gartner a professor worth having.

This class was epic! Prof. Gartner was awesome and explained the concepts very clearly. The marking depended heavily on the TA. One of the TA's was just too harsh and felt like she knew everything (Holly C) If you have her then  do everything you can to switch. Otherwise, the course material was interesting and prof. Gartner spiced things up !

Very knowledgable and organized professor. Lectures were interesting and she always engaged the class in fun ways (interesting questions, short 2 question surveys followed by discussions). Essay was basically a film analysis using course ideas - one of the only enjoyable papers in my university career.
